@{B}FDC_HIDE_B=no@{b} or
@{B}FDC_HIDE_B=yes@{b}
This 'hides' (removes from the list of valid system drives) the
floppy disk B:. Of course, this is only useful on systems, where
the floppy B: is not present physically. The default is 'no'.

@{B}KBD_AT_CAPS=no@{b} or
@{B}KBD_AT_CAPS=yes@{b}
When this is set to "YES", the CapsLock and Shift keys operate as on
PC/AT keyboard, i.e. the Shift key reverses the state of the Caps:
holding shift produces upper case letters, unless the Caps is
active.

