@node "Special keys"
@toc "Appendices"

@line 1 70 0

When the virtual console daemon is installed, function keys F1-F9
in conjunction with the Alt key, activate virtual text consoles,
which are marked enbled by the /etc/ttytab file. Alt/F10 returns to
the 'real', graphic console.

Despite that, all versions of FreeMiNT handle the following
keyboard shortcuts:

@{B}Ctrl/Alt/Del@{b}
Warm start, as in all TOS versions.

@{B}Ctrl/Alt/RShift/Del@{b}
Cold start, as in TOS version >= 1.04.

@{B}Ctrl/Alt/LShift/Del@{b}
Halts the system and powers it off, whenever possible.

@{B}Ctrl/Alt/Undo@{b}
Sends SIGQUIT to the whole group of processes running on the
console, including the shell. This is equal to a "logout", but
don't use it while using the GEM Desktop! :-)

@{B}Left Shift@{b}
When you hold down the left Shift key while booting FreeMiNT, it
will either ask you whether it should load itself or not (kernels
before 1.16.0) or whether it should display the boot menu or not
(kernels 1.16.0 and later).

@{B}Alt/Up@{b}, @{B}Alt/Down@{b}, @{B}Alt/Left@{b}, @{B}Alt/Right@{b}
Move the mouse cursor in the specified direction. The mouse cursor is
moved for 8 pixels, unless you hold down the Shift key: the movement
distance is 1 pixel at once then.

@{B}Alt/Insert@{b}, @{B}Alt/ClrHome@{b}
Emulate left and right mouse click, respectively. Unlike on TOS, the
Alternate key is ignored, when processing mouse events.

@{B}Shift/Alt/Insert@{b}
Emulate double click of the left mouse button.

